-- Vazquez Mota Leads in Primary for Presidency, PAN Says
-- B y   B e n   B a i n
-- 2012-02-06T02:52:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/vazquez-mota-leads-in-primary-for-presidency-pan-says.html
Josefina Vazquez Mota, a former
education minister, is leading in a primary election to be
 Mexico ’s National Action Party’s candidate for president,
according to the party’s chief election coordinator.  Vazquez Mota, 51, the only woman contending for the July 1
presidential election, is leading the preliminary results with
55 percent of the vote, Jose Espina told reporters.  Ernesto Cordero , a former finance minister, has 38.1
percent of the vote, while Santiago Creel, who was interior
minister during the administration of Vicente Fox, was third
with 6.1 percent, according to Espina.  More than 1.8 million party members were slated to vote
today, according to Vazquez Mota’s  website .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Bain in Mexico City at 
